Shh!

14
00:01:54,444 --> 00:01:55,739
Take them all out.

15
00:02:11,384 --> 00:02:12,206
Wayu.

16
00:02:16,775 --> 00:02:17,750
Wayu.

17
00:02:23,064 --> 00:02:24,154
Wayu.

18
00:02:43,021 --> 00:02:44,073
Can you stand?

19
00:02:45,258 --> 00:02:46,749
Ugh...

20
00:02:48,106 --> 00:02:48,986
You okay?

21
00:02:52,159 --> 00:02:54,759
Krit, I hear someone.

22
00:02:55,542 --> 00:02:57,206
Let's go. Can you walk?

23
00:02:57,244 --> 00:02:58,333
- I can.
- Let's go.

24
00:03:07,758 --> 00:03:09,115
Help!

25
00:03:10,874 --> 00:03:12,250
Help!

26
00:03:12,900 --> 00:03:14,525
Help!

27
00:03:18,157 --> 00:03:20,126
Is anyone there?

28
00:03:21,999 --> 00:03:23,567
Help!

29
00:03:28,078 --> 00:03:28,824
Hey!

30
00:03:29,607 --> 00:03:34,960
Help!

31
00:03:35,801 --> 00:03:38,171
Don't! Don't come in!

32
00:03:39,739 --> 00:03:40,981
It's locked, Krit.

33
00:03:42,358 --> 00:03:44,327
I've got the victims.
They're on the third floor.

34
00:03:44,613 --> 00:03:47,137
Search every room.
Then start the operation.

35
00:04:02,162 --> 00:04:04,972
Hey, we're the police. We're the police.

36
00:04:07,878 --> 00:04:10,363
Seal all the exits.
Don't let them get away.

37
00:04:31,563 --> 00:04:32,614
What's going on?

38
00:04:36,074 --> 00:04:38,349
I said what's going on?

39
00:04:40,604 --> 00:04:42,115
You're about to get arrested!

40
00:04:42,860 --> 00:04:44,217
You'd better hide well.

41
00:04:49,838 --> 00:04:51,214
Hehe.

42
00:04:53,833 --> 00:04:55,496
Oh! Sir.

43
00:04:58,057 --> 00:05:00,581
The cops are burning this whole place.
Let's get out of here.

44
00:05:00,753 --> 00:05:02,454
I've got a chopper ready for you, Sir.

45
00:05:08,113 --> 00:05:09,393
Okay.

46
00:05:51,410 --> 00:05:52,385
Surprise!

47
00:05:54,584 --> 00:05:57,489
The chopper's late.
You can't get out in time.

48
00:05:59,802 --> 00:06:02,670
There are two exits,
the front door and the back door.

49
00:06:03,587 --> 00:06:04,964
We have to force them out.

50
00:06:05,843 --> 00:06:07,277
So what should we do?

51
00:06:10,909 --> 00:06:12,840
- Burn the building.
- Huh?

52
00:06:13,585 --> 00:06:15,267
Isn't that dangerous, Captain?

53
00:06:17,236 --> 00:06:18,899
Who said we're really going to burn it?

54
00:06:24,844 --> 00:06:26,488
Once we've successfully rescued
the victims,

55
00:06:26,488 --> 00:06:28,553
we'll use smoke bombs to force them out.

56
00:06:29,165 --> 00:06:31,325
Send people to block both exits.

57
00:06:31,841 --> 00:06:33,179
And around the whole building.

58
00:06:33,695 --> 00:06:35,224
I'll go up to the rooftop.

59
00:06:35,645 --> 00:06:37,920
In case they try to escape by chopper.

60
00:06:58,126 --> 00:06:59,215
Wayu.

61
00:07:14,890 --> 00:07:15,961
Be careful.

62
00:08:39,555 --> 00:08:41,582
Haha.

63
00:08:42,021 --> 00:08:42,843
Krit.

64
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:44,640
Krit.

65
00:08:58,155 --> 00:08:59,857
If you're so tough, come in!

66
00:09:00,373 --> 00:09:02,418
Shoot, and we both die.

67
00:09:03,890 --> 00:09:07,255
- Put the gun down. Don't touch him.
- You, put it down.

68
00:09:08,077 --> 00:09:10,466
And let me walk away.

69
00:09:15,150 --> 00:09:16,220
Put the gun down.

70
00:09:16,927 --> 00:09:17,788
Hurry.

71
00:09:17,788 --> 00:09:19,929
Oh, wow.

72
00:09:21,879 --> 00:09:24,727
Bring Wayu to me, and I'll let you go.

73
00:09:27,957 --> 00:09:28,837
- Bang.
- Wayu!

74
00:09:28,837 --> 00:09:32,067
Haha.

75
00:09:32,182 --> 00:09:33,864
Ouch.

76
00:09:34,266 --> 00:09:35,986
You really love him, huh?

77
00:09:37,382 --> 00:09:38,433
Wow.

78
00:09:39,217 --> 00:09:43,977
A love affair between a spy
and a cop? What a cliche.

79
00:09:47,054 --> 00:09:50,036
Sigh, since I can't have you anyway,

80
00:09:51,069 --> 00:09:53,592
I'll at least leave you with a scar.

81
00:09:54,242 --> 00:09:55,771
Wayu, throw!

82
00:10:03,456 --> 00:10:06,457
Wayu, are you hurt?

83
00:10:06,897 --> 00:10:07,986
I'm okay.

84
00:10:08,503 --> 00:10:11,122
- Ouch.
- I'm okay.

85
00:10:14,390 --> 00:10:17,276
Don't worry. I'm right here now.

86
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:21,234
Krit.

87
00:10:41,096 --> 00:10:42,090
Krit.

88
00:10:44,651 --> 00:10:47,442
- I'm fine.
- Krit.

89
00:10:50,443 --> 00:10:51,781
You're fine.

90
00:10:52,661 --> 00:10:53,750
I'm glad.

91
00:10:57,096 --> 00:11:00,498
Call an ambulance, please.

92
00:11:03,786 --> 00:11:05,908
Krit!

93
00:11:10,305 --> 00:11:11,089
Krit.

94
00:11:15,218 --> 00:11:16,919
- Krit.
- Family can't come in here.

95
00:11:16,919 --> 00:11:18,277
- Krit.
- Family can't come in here.

96
00:11:18,277 --> 00:11:19,194
Please wait out front.

97
00:11:19,194 --> 00:11:20,202
Can I go in to see him?

98
00:11:20,202 --> 00:11:22,367
Family can't come in here.
Please wait out front.

99
00:11:54,023 --> 00:11:56,738
Wayu, how is Krit?

100
00:12:00,351 --> 00:12:01,995
He's been in there for two hours now.

101
00:12:02,779 --> 00:12:04,595
He still hasn't come out.

102
00:12:09,660 --> 00:12:11,648
- Ma'am.
- Darling.

103
00:12:13,484 --> 00:12:14,879
Why don't you go sit down for a bit?

104
00:12:16,370 --> 00:12:17,077
Hey, darling.

105
00:12:18,224 --> 00:12:19,467
It's this kid.

106
00:12:20,346 --> 00:12:22,430
He's the one who made Krit lose his way.

107
00:12:23,003 --> 00:12:26,119
Sir, let's go sit down
and wait for the doctor.

108
00:12:27,324 --> 00:12:28,624
Stop seeing Krit.

109
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,892
If you're a leech,
go cling to someone else.

110
00:12:32,561 --> 00:12:35,238
Stop leeching off my son
and turning him into a freak.

111
00:12:35,238 --> 00:12:36,595
It's disgusting.

112
00:12:38,564 --> 00:12:39,386
Sir.

113
00:12:40,934 --> 00:12:43,534
I don't know where you got
this kind of logic from.

114
00:12:44,585 --> 00:12:47,281
But I've never once thought about
leeching off Krit as you said, Sir.

115
00:12:48,332 --> 00:12:51,333
- We're together because we're in love.
- Love? Really?

116
00:12:52,117 --> 00:12:53,857
You only love yourself.

117
00:12:54,640 --> 00:12:55,940
If you really love Krit,

118
00:12:56,896 --> 00:12:58,827
you should stay out of his life.

119
00:12:59,286 --> 00:13:01,063
Let him live a good life.

120
00:13:01,159 --> 00:13:04,294
- Not on someone with no future.
- Sir.

121
00:13:04,371 --> 00:13:05,479
That's enough.

122
00:13:08,825 --> 00:13:10,488
Wayu, go back for now.

123
00:13:12,227 --> 00:13:13,030
No.

124
00:13:13,546 --> 00:13:15,764
I'm staying here until Krit wakes up.

125
00:13:15,764 --> 00:13:16,968
What are you still waiting for?

126
00:13:18,077 --> 00:13:19,969
He is like this because of you.

127
00:13:20,696 --> 00:13:22,149
If anything happens to him,

128
00:13:24,232 --> 00:13:25,666
it'll be all your fault.

129
00:13:28,247 --> 00:13:29,202
Remember that.

130
00:13:30,540 --> 00:13:31,745
Calm down.

131
00:13:32,146 --> 00:13:34,536
This is a hospital. That's enough.

132
00:13:34,536 --> 00:13:36,715
- That's enough.
- Step outside.

133
00:13:37,231 --> 00:13:38,416
Just step outside.

134
00:14:00,839 --> 00:14:01,623
Here.

135
00:14:11,525 --> 00:14:12,481
Thank you.

136
00:14:16,133 --> 00:14:16,630
Hey.

137
00:14:17,222 --> 00:14:20,835
Don't overthink it.
Krit's dad just spoke out of anger.

138
00:14:27,143 --> 00:14:28,921
If Krit hadn't come to help me,

139
00:14:29,915 --> 00:14:32,113
he wouldn't have to go through this.

140
00:14:34,771 --> 00:14:37,542
If you get hurt
or anything happens to you,

141
00:14:38,498 --> 00:14:40,601
Krit would be just as hurt.

142
00:14:45,801 --> 00:14:47,215
Maybe it was like that before.

143
00:14:49,108 --> 00:14:51,287
But not now anymore.

144
00:14:57,557 --> 00:14:58,551
That's not true.

145
00:15:01,055 --> 00:15:02,756
Krit never abandoned you, Wayu.

146
00:15:04,343 --> 00:15:06,408
He's always been looking out for you.

147
00:15:09,963 --> 00:15:10,995
Krit...

148
00:15:13,156 --> 00:15:14,551
He hasn't moved on.

149
00:15:27,149 --> 00:15:29,404
Wayu, just go back for today.

150
00:15:30,073 --> 00:15:33,228
Wait until Krit's dad cools down,
and then come visit again.

151
00:15:33,591 --> 00:15:35,005
I'll talk to him for you.

152
00:15:35,311 --> 00:15:38,007
And I'll keep you updated
on how Krit's doing.

153
00:15:42,881 --> 00:15:45,749
Even if I go back,
I still won't be able to sleep.

154
00:15:48,042 --> 00:15:49,744
I'd rather stay here

155
00:15:50,069 --> 00:15:52,764
until I'm sure he is safe.

156
00:15:57,887 --> 00:16:01,347
Okay, that's fine.

157
00:17:13,874 --> 00:17:14,925
Doctor.

158
00:17:16,665 --> 00:17:18,462
- How is he?
- Doctor.

159
00:17:18,462 --> 00:17:20,201
How is my son doing?

160
00:17:24,273 --> 00:17:26,337
The surgery went well.

161
00:17:26,337 --> 00:17:28,268
The patient is out of danger now.

162
00:17:33,353 --> 00:17:34,672
During the surgery,

163
00:17:34,672 --> 00:17:37,902
the patient lost a lot of blood,
and his heart stopped for two minutes.

164
00:17:37,902 --> 00:17:39,902
So, we put in a breathing tube.

165
00:17:40,081 --> 00:17:42,375
We managed to revive him.

166
00:17:42,375 --> 00:17:45,600
Will this have any
repercussions for him?

167
00:17:46,696 --> 00:17:49,697
From what I can see right now,
there's nothing to worry about.

168
00:17:49,774 --> 00:17:53,157
We'll wait for him to wake up,
and run a full check.

169
00:17:53,654 --> 00:17:54,782
Oh, okay.

170
00:17:54,878 --> 00:17:56,407
- I'll take my leave.
- Alright.

171
00:17:56,407 --> 00:17:57,955
- Thank you very much.
- Thank you.

172
00:18:22,233 --> 00:18:25,119
Police have arrested Irfan Faruhanan,
also known as Ice.

173
00:18:25,119 --> 00:18:26,649
A Thai-Malaysian national.

174
00:18:26,649 --> 00:18:28,943
On charges of human
and organ trafficking.

175
00:18:29,115 --> 00:18:31,217
He was also found in possession
of illegal drugs.

176
00:18:31,217 --> 00:18:35,021
Ice was backed by Por,
who financed him from behind the scenes.

177
00:18:42,075 --> 00:18:44,121
Wow, you're done already?

178
00:18:47,982 --> 00:18:52,035
Thanks a lot for your cooperation
with today's questioning.

179
00:18:53,105 --> 00:18:56,087
You're welcome. If you need
anything else, just let me know.

180
00:18:56,393 --> 00:18:57,273
Sure thing.

181
00:18:57,846 --> 00:19:00,733
If there's nothing else,
I'll get back to work.

182
00:19:00,924 --> 00:19:02,510
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

183
00:19:05,492 --> 00:19:08,876
Hey, let's go grab
something good to eat.

184
00:19:09,048 --> 00:19:09,794
Go.

185
00:19:10,424 --> 00:19:12,355
Hey, you can totally trust me.

186
00:19:12,355 --> 00:19:15,509
I'll take you to get something
seriously unhealthy.

187
00:19:15,509 --> 00:19:16,618
Right, man?

188
00:19:22,104 --> 00:19:23,780
(Rose)
(Krit's parents aren't here.)

189
00:19:23,780 --> 00:19:25,450
(Visit whenever you want.)

190
00:19:28,126 --> 00:19:29,636
Come to the hospital with me, yeah?

191
00:19:31,204 --> 00:19:33,326
Are you going to eat hospital
health food or what?

192
00:20:09,245 --> 00:20:11,156
I brought you some flowers, Krit.

193
00:20:14,903 --> 00:20:17,751
So the room will smell nice.

194
00:20:20,045 --> 00:20:21,441
I don't know...

195
00:20:22,549 --> 00:20:26,354
if your parents
found out I brought them.

196
00:20:32,987 --> 00:20:36,122
If they ever knew,
they'd probably be angry.

197
00:20:40,194 --> 00:20:41,952
Why do we have to hide like this?

198
00:20:42,564 --> 00:20:45,603
Can't people just care about
each other? Huh?

199
00:20:46,043 --> 00:20:47,936
Relationships are one thing.

200
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:50,325
Being human is another. Right?

201
00:20:50,650 --> 00:20:53,174
I really don't get it.

202
00:20:57,379 --> 00:21:00,801
They're probably scared
I'll get back together with Krit.

203
00:21:04,375 --> 00:21:07,224
What matters now
is the captain's health.

204
00:21:07,663 --> 00:21:09,651
He still hasn't woken up.

205
00:21:31,883 --> 00:21:35,229
Uh... Sorry, I didn't know
someone was here.

206
00:21:35,324 --> 00:21:37,045
It's okay. Please go ahead.

207
00:21:37,255 --> 00:21:39,300
Go ahead. Walk carefully, okay?

208
00:21:39,300 --> 00:21:41,996
It's okay. I'm just dropping by
for a bit.

209
00:21:41,996 --> 00:21:44,710
Besides, Krit hasn't woken up anyway.

210
00:21:52,414 --> 00:21:57,059
Uh, are you a friend of Krit's
or his junior?

211
00:21:57,270 --> 00:22:00,366
Uh, I'm his fiancée.

212
00:22:02,335 --> 00:22:05,450
Once he wakes up,
we'll probably get married.

213
00:22:05,450 --> 00:22:07,458
That's what my dad said.

214
00:22:17,399 --> 00:22:19,502
Yes, yes.

215
00:22:22,140 --> 00:22:25,504
If he wakes up, please tell him

216
00:22:25,504 --> 00:22:27,186
that Mint brought him a melon.

217
00:22:27,741 --> 00:22:29,633
- Yes.
- Okay, I'm coming.

218
00:22:30,226 --> 00:22:32,806
Yes, okay.

219
00:22:37,050 --> 00:22:39,707
That girl? Seriously?

220
00:22:40,835 --> 00:22:42,269
But she's pretty cute.

221
00:22:43,683 --> 00:22:45,079
But I think she's too young.

222
00:22:45,289 --> 00:22:46,818
What do the adults even think?

223
00:22:46,895 --> 00:22:49,514
Or is a good family name
all that matters?

224
00:22:51,808 --> 00:22:54,561
I'm with you on this one.

225
00:22:54,812 --> 00:22:56,526
You're a better match.

226
00:22:58,001 --> 00:23:00,429
I'm serious, look at them.

227
00:23:00,697 --> 00:23:02,111
You just fit him better.

228
00:23:04,941 --> 00:23:06,527
She's pretty cute though.

229
00:23:08,974 --> 00:23:10,427
Did you get hurt anywhere?

230
00:23:10,618 --> 00:23:13,218
Hey. You're okay, right?

231
00:23:15,263 --> 00:23:16,601
I'm alright, Mom.

232
00:23:16,773 --> 00:23:21,495
Oh, dear. It's okay,
my child. It's okay.

233
00:23:21,495 --> 00:23:25,070
After all that, you must've been
scared to death.

234
00:23:25,299 --> 00:23:26,848
Yeah, right.

235
00:23:26,848 --> 00:23:31,282
When Mom and I heard you'd been
kidnapped, we were so worried.

236
00:23:31,282 --> 00:23:33,615
Why keep something this big
all to yourself?

237
00:23:37,056 --> 00:23:39,388
I'm really sorry.

238
00:23:39,961 --> 00:23:42,045
I've just had a lot to deal with.

239
00:23:44,549 --> 00:23:45,677
I'm sorry too.

240
00:23:47,264 --> 00:23:48,066
Yeah.

241
00:23:48,468 --> 00:23:49,538
And the captain?

242
00:23:50,437 --> 00:23:53,572
I saw on the news that
the captain was badly hurt.

243
00:24:03,283 --> 00:24:06,934
Captain... He was shot.

244
00:24:10,356 --> 00:24:11,159
But...

245
00:24:13,433 --> 00:24:16,530
He's safe now.
He just hasn't woken up yet.

246
00:24:18,193 --> 00:24:19,895
He'll wake up soon. He'll wake up.

247
00:24:19,895 --> 00:24:21,787
He'll be fine, okay?

248
00:24:22,017 --> 00:24:23,565
Don't think too much about it yet.

249
00:24:23,909 --> 00:24:27,484
Good karma protecting good people.

250
00:24:29,931 --> 00:24:32,989
You're not just stressed
about Captain not waking up, right?

251
00:24:36,162 --> 00:24:37,386
What else is going on?

252
00:24:40,196 --> 00:24:41,228
Tell us everything.

253
00:24:47,460 --> 00:24:49,582
He is getting married.

254
00:24:49,582 --> 00:24:50,385
What?

255
00:24:50,614 --> 00:24:53,233
Wait, married? Married to whom?

256
00:24:53,233 --> 00:24:54,896
And how do you know?

257
00:24:55,699 --> 00:24:56,540
Sigh.

258
00:24:57,745 --> 00:25:00,115
Well, today...

259
00:25:00,612 --> 00:25:03,001
I went to visit him
at the hospital today and...

260
00:25:03,651 --> 00:25:05,276
I ran into his fiancée.

261
00:25:07,131 --> 00:25:08,373
What the heck?

262
00:25:10,380 --> 00:25:12,196
Captain and I shouldn't have met at all.

263
00:25:13,974 --> 00:25:16,153
Ending it like that
was probably for the best.

264
00:25:17,988 --> 00:25:20,512
It's already bad enough
that his parents don't like me.

265
00:25:22,060 --> 00:25:23,914
And now I've even met his fiancée.

266
00:25:24,889 --> 00:25:26,954
Hey, it's really fine.

267
00:25:26,954 --> 00:25:30,089
Good-looking people like you
can find plenty of partners.

268
00:25:30,318 --> 00:25:32,975
Don't get hung up on just one guy, okay?

269
00:25:35,116 --> 00:25:35,958
Really?

270
00:25:38,404 --> 00:25:41,444
If he already has a fiancée,
why's he taking care of Singto?

271
00:25:44,885 --> 00:25:45,649
What?

272
00:25:46,968 --> 00:25:49,129
- Krit, right?
- Yeah.

273
00:25:50,008 --> 00:25:53,736
You broke up with Wayu.
Why are you still looking after Singto?

274
00:25:54,997 --> 00:25:57,196
I'm just keeping the promise
I made to Wayu.

275
00:26:05,568 --> 00:26:06,734
But Wai, don't worry.

276
00:26:07,346 --> 00:26:09,468
If Singto starts to improve,

277
00:26:10,156 --> 00:26:11,322
I'll back off for good.

278
00:26:12,603 --> 00:26:14,171
You still love Wayu, right?

279
00:26:20,039 --> 00:26:22,314
If you still love him,
then why break up?

280
00:26:22,505 --> 00:26:24,551
Why make things so hard?

281
00:26:30,266 --> 00:26:31,796
Don't tell Wayu about this.

282
00:26:32,579 --> 00:26:34,567
He doesn't need to worry about this.

283
00:26:35,734 --> 00:26:37,282
He deserves someone good.

284
00:26:39,174 --> 00:26:42,769
(He even hired a psychologist
to look after Singto at school.)

285
00:26:42,769 --> 00:26:45,406
(And he secretly comes
to see Singto all the time.)

286
00:26:45,406 --> 00:26:48,178
I'm sure Krit still loves you.
I really am.

287
00:26:56,111 --> 00:26:58,921
About the marriage,
I'm sure it's arranged.

288
00:26:58,921 --> 00:27:01,693
Rich people love marrying
their kids off for business.

289
00:27:02,592 --> 00:27:06,033
Yeah. I've seen it in dramas.

290
00:27:06,663 --> 00:27:09,225
Yeah, it might sound cheesy.

291
00:27:09,225 --> 00:27:13,105
But you've got to listen
to your own heart.

292
00:27:14,425 --> 00:27:16,833
You want to visit him, right?
Then just go.

293
00:27:16,833 --> 00:27:19,356
If you want to do something
for him, then do it.

294
00:27:19,395 --> 00:27:21,860
He's already done so much for you.

295
00:27:21,860 --> 00:27:23,677
I think it's clear enough.

296
00:27:24,250 --> 00:27:27,328
Now it's time for you
to be clear with him too.

297
00:28:07,835 --> 00:28:08,733
Mm.

298
00:28:10,530 --> 00:28:12,652
Sorry, no visitors are allowed
in this room.

299
00:28:14,946 --> 00:28:17,030
Rose told me to come here.

300
00:28:17,546 --> 00:28:18,827
Is she inside?

301
00:28:19,438 --> 00:28:21,962
Rose didn't tell us anything.
Please step outside.

302
00:28:23,606 --> 00:28:24,925
Oh, come on, Officer.

303
00:28:25,020 --> 00:28:26,951
With a face like mine,
I couldn't hurt anyone.

304
00:28:27,257 --> 00:28:28,633
Please let me in.

305
00:28:29,685 --> 00:28:30,908
- No, you can't.
- No way.

306
00:28:33,794 --> 00:28:35,840
I told you, I'm here on Rose's orders.

307
00:28:35,916 --> 00:28:37,484
Let me in, please.

308
00:28:39,147 --> 00:28:40,523
No, you can't.

309
00:28:45,857 --> 00:28:46,640
Oh.

310
00:28:47,767 --> 00:28:49,881
Wayu, are you okay?

311
00:28:51,114 --> 00:28:53,885
These two officers won't let me go in.

312
00:28:55,874 --> 00:28:57,995
Sorry, I forgot to tell them.

313
00:29:02,125 --> 00:29:05,833
From now on, if he comes,
please let him in.

314
00:29:07,037 --> 00:29:09,389
If anything happens,
I'll take responsibility.

315
00:29:09,542 --> 00:29:10,708
- Okay.
- Sure.

316
00:29:26,670 --> 00:29:28,753
Thank you for letting me in.

317
00:29:29,996 --> 00:29:31,794
At first there was no guard, right?

318
00:29:31,794 --> 00:29:33,800
Then why have someone now, Rose?

319
00:29:34,392 --> 00:29:39,114
Krit's dad worried that Ice's men
or Por's might still be around.

320
00:29:39,114 --> 00:29:41,676
So he had someone guard Krit,
just to be safe.

321
00:29:45,270 --> 00:29:46,264
Yeah.

322
00:29:46,799 --> 00:29:49,456
Then please look after him for me.

323
00:29:50,163 --> 00:29:53,833
Today, his parents went back,
so the coast is clear.

324
00:29:54,311 --> 00:29:55,764
I'll come back again this evening.

325
00:29:56,605 --> 00:29:57,542
Thank you.

326
00:29:57,848 --> 00:29:58,746
Bye.

327
00:30:24,687 --> 00:30:26,140
Sleep well.

328
00:30:27,057 --> 00:30:28,548
Aren't you bored yet, Krit?

329
00:30:28,816 --> 00:30:30,231
Wake up and see me already.

330
00:30:37,418 --> 00:30:38,240
Mm.

331
00:30:40,362 --> 00:30:43,975
Hey, I've got something to show you.

332
00:30:48,620 --> 00:30:51,468
See, am I awesome or what, Krit?

333
00:30:52,902 --> 00:30:56,477
I've seen people doing this
for their partners lately.

334
00:31:00,835 --> 00:31:02,021
I mean, for their exes.

335
00:31:05,175 --> 00:31:06,322
But forget it, it's all good.

336
00:31:06,513 --> 00:31:08,214
Current or ex,

337
00:31:08,520 --> 00:31:10,661
I just made it for you.

338
00:31:12,515 --> 00:31:14,389
Wake up and praise me already.

339
00:31:16,071 --> 00:31:17,046
You know?

340
00:31:20,563 --> 00:31:21,806
I'm waiting for you.

341
00:31:38,590 --> 00:31:40,253
- Oh.
- Oh, Rose?

342
00:31:40,406 --> 00:31:43,082
Where are you going, dear?
Not staying to watch over Krit?

343
00:31:43,426 --> 00:31:45,032
Uh, I...

344
00:31:46,045 --> 00:31:48,549
I'm just going down
to pick something up from the rider.

345
00:31:48,549 --> 00:31:50,556
- I ordered some coffee.
- Oh, really?

346
00:31:50,977 --> 00:31:53,825
I saw you bring a bag
and thought you were going home.

347
00:31:54,360 --> 00:31:57,534
Oh, I just grabbed it on my way out.

348
00:31:57,629 --> 00:32:00,191
- Hmm.
- Let's go.

349
00:32:00,631 --> 00:32:03,117
Aren't you heading straight home?

350
00:32:03,117 --> 00:32:04,320
You said you had errands.

351
00:32:04,836 --> 00:32:06,824
He forgot his phone, that's all.

352
00:32:06,824 --> 00:32:07,971
We'll hurry back for it.

353
00:32:07,971 --> 00:32:11,068
You hurry down and get your things.
I'll see you in the room.

354
00:32:11,144 --> 00:32:12,540
- Okay.
- Come on, let's go.

355
00:32:13,228 --> 00:32:14,929
- Sir.
- Hmm?

356
00:32:14,929 --> 00:32:17,510
I just checked and didn't see it.

357
00:32:17,720 --> 00:32:19,689
Maybe you left it somewhere else?

358
00:32:20,416 --> 00:32:21,907
I left it in the room.

359
00:32:22,155 --> 00:32:26,396
But I checked just now, um...
It's not there.

360
00:32:26,896 --> 00:32:29,916
- Maybe you left it at home.
- No.

361
00:32:29,916 --> 00:32:31,809
I went to the bathroom
and left it there.

362
00:32:31,885 --> 00:32:33,185
It's in there, I'm sure.

363
00:32:33,587 --> 00:32:35,039
Let's go before traffic gets bad.

364
00:32:44,005 --> 00:32:45,668
Sir, Ma'am.

365
00:32:46,738 --> 00:32:48,344
- Hmm?
- I think...

366
00:32:48,516 --> 00:32:50,256
Better to let Krit rest.

367
00:32:50,256 --> 00:32:53,257
All this coming and going
isn't good for his health.

368
00:32:54,366 --> 00:32:57,520
I think it'll be fine. I'm just grabbing
my phone and heading out.

369
00:32:59,126 --> 00:33:00,559
- I mean...
- Rose.

370
00:33:00,751 --> 00:33:02,892
What's going on? What's wrong with Krit?

371
00:33:04,077 --> 00:33:08,588
Uh, no... Krit is not... Um, Sir...

372
00:33:09,945 --> 00:33:11,016
Ma'am.

373
00:33:29,463 --> 00:33:30,763
- Here it is, darling.
- Ah.

374
00:33:34,089 --> 00:33:34,949
Good.

375
00:33:35,274 --> 00:33:37,759
In that case, I'll go run my errands.

376
00:33:38,199 --> 00:33:41,238
Anyway, look after Krit for me.
I'll be back soon.

377
00:33:41,640 --> 00:33:43,284
- Sure, Ma'am.
- Tell me if you need anything.

378
00:33:43,284 --> 00:33:44,641
- Let's go, darling.
- Uh-huh.

379
00:33:44,832 --> 00:33:47,757
No need to rush, Ma'am.
I can take care of Krit.

380
00:33:49,669 --> 00:33:51,045
- Darling.
- Wait.

381
00:34:25,225 --> 00:34:26,429
Hello, Sir.

382
00:34:29,411 --> 00:34:30,634
Why are you here again?

383
00:34:32,355 --> 00:34:35,375
Can I take care of Krit
until he wakes up?

384
00:34:36,579 --> 00:34:39,160
He saved my life, Sir.
I just want to repay him.

385
00:34:40,823 --> 00:34:41,569
Ugh.

386
00:34:42,353 --> 00:34:44,264
Sir, please just hear me out first.

387
00:34:45,430 --> 00:34:47,992
If you want to repay him,
then don't show your face here again.

388
00:34:49,884 --> 00:34:52,465
What else do you want? What do you need?

389
00:34:53,459 --> 00:34:55,256
Your work always needs money, right?

390
00:34:56,250 --> 00:34:57,760
Tell me how much you want.

391
00:34:58,085 --> 00:35:00,704
- Is a million enough?
- Sir, that's too harsh.

392
00:35:01,832 --> 00:35:04,240
Wayu just wants to be here
to take care of Krit.

393
00:35:04,967 --> 00:35:06,859
Ma'am, please say something.

394
00:35:06,948 --> 00:35:09,464
He really doesn't have
any bad intentions.

395
00:35:11,849 --> 00:35:12,671
Sir.

396
00:35:12,805 --> 00:35:14,773
I don't want money
or anything like that.

397
00:35:15,767 --> 00:35:18,386
I just want to make sure he is safe.

398
00:35:18,539 --> 00:35:19,858
That's all, Sir.

399
00:35:20,202 --> 00:35:21,483
Have you forgotten already?

400
00:35:22,190 --> 00:35:24,064
Who do you think made Krit
end up like this?

401
00:35:24,484 --> 00:35:26,778
And now you're so worried
about his safety, huh?

402
00:35:28,977 --> 00:35:30,468
- Sergeant.
- Yes, Sir.

403
00:35:31,959 --> 00:35:33,890
Please give me a chance, Sir.

404
00:35:33,890 --> 00:35:35,648
- Let me take care of Krit.
- Get him out of here.

405
00:35:35,744 --> 00:35:37,178
- Come on.
- Sir.

406
00:35:38,114 --> 00:35:38,936
Go.

407
00:35:39,911 --> 00:35:41,096
- Sir.
- Go.

408
00:35:41,096 --> 00:35:43,581
- Sir.
- And don't let him back in.

409
00:35:43,581 --> 00:35:44,556
Understood.

410
00:35:45,206 --> 00:35:46,430
- Go
- Sir.

411
00:35:47,003 --> 00:35:49,010
Sir!

412
00:36:04,093 --> 00:36:07,171
What do high-ranking officers like?

413
00:36:08,853 --> 00:36:11,950
Status, image, classy stuff.

414
00:36:12,236 --> 00:36:13,555
Luxury watches.

415
00:36:14,435 --> 00:36:17,837
Tai, should I give the watch
the clients gave me

416
00:36:17,933 --> 00:36:19,290
to Krit's dad?

417
00:36:19,367 --> 00:36:20,820
Huh, yeah, that's good.

418
00:36:20,820 --> 00:36:22,941
Then he'll know you've got a sugar mom.

419
00:36:23,133 --> 00:36:25,771
It's not hard to trace those watches.
They can see who bought them.

420
00:36:25,943 --> 00:36:27,950
There are only a few
in the whole country.

421
00:36:28,504 --> 00:36:30,989
Next topic.

422
00:36:31,448 --> 00:36:33,895
Social networks and parties, right?

423
00:36:33,895 --> 00:36:37,661
He probably doesn't care about
the bar host scene or college circles.

424
00:36:38,578 --> 00:36:41,598
He likes people who respect him
and follow orders.

425
00:36:41,598 --> 00:36:43,204
And you keep arguing with him like that.

426
00:36:43,319 --> 00:36:44,753
You'd call that following orders?

427
00:36:46,512 --> 00:36:49,914
Then, things or activities
that show status.

428
00:36:49,914 --> 00:36:52,610
Like guns and amulets.

429
00:36:53,642 --> 00:36:54,846
Guns?

430
00:36:54,846 --> 00:36:58,249
Then I'll buy a gun for Krit's dad.
I bet he'll love it.

431
00:36:58,249 --> 00:37:01,422
Yeah, good idea. So he can shoot you
when you go see his son.

432
00:37:01,422 --> 00:37:03,812
Can you stop with the digs, Tai? Huh?

433
00:37:03,812 --> 00:37:06,832
So are you on Krit's dad's side,
or mine?

434
00:37:06,832 --> 00:37:08,323
Here's my advice.

435
00:37:08,343 --> 00:37:10,198
Just give up.

436
00:37:10,233 --> 00:37:12,233
People their age
don't change their minds easily.

437
00:37:12,242 --> 00:37:13,656
Just stop trying.

438
00:37:13,809 --> 00:37:15,186
I feel sorry for you.

439
00:37:16,964 --> 00:37:20,022
No. I'm never giving up. No way.

440
00:37:20,022 --> 00:37:22,928
At least not until Krit wakes up.

441
00:37:23,539 --> 00:37:25,623
- I'll take care of him myself.
- Wow.

442
00:37:25,719 --> 00:37:28,471
Love really does make
people blind. Sigh.

443
00:37:31,109 --> 00:37:32,256
Let me tell you something.

444
00:37:32,256 --> 00:37:35,066
People at that level,
they don't need anything.

445
00:37:35,315 --> 00:37:38,106
They just want to know
if you truly love their child.

446
00:37:38,106 --> 00:37:38,966
That's it.

447
00:37:39,597 --> 00:37:41,050
So,

448
00:37:41,568 --> 00:37:43,969
being consistent might actually help.

449
00:37:46,727 --> 00:37:48,658
That's good then.

450
00:37:48,964 --> 00:37:51,067
I'll fight back with pure sincerity.

451
00:37:52,538 --> 00:37:54,756
Yeah, that's how it should be, man.

452
00:38:11,807 --> 00:38:15,267
- Please send the BP report for Room 3 quickly.
- Right away.

453
00:38:35,607 --> 00:38:38,149
- Hello.
- Oh, hello.

454
00:38:38,589 --> 00:38:41,036
I've brought fruit for everyone.

455
00:38:42,642 --> 00:38:43,827
Thank you.

456
00:38:44,955 --> 00:38:45,987
And...

457
00:38:47,363 --> 00:38:50,479
Could you please change the flowers
in Captain Krit's room?

458
00:38:51,989 --> 00:38:53,997
It's just that...

459
00:38:54,073 --> 00:38:56,367
I was a victim in Captain Krit's case.

460
00:38:56,788 --> 00:38:58,852
But right now,
they're not allowing visits.

461
00:38:59,598 --> 00:39:00,936
So I can't go in.

462
00:39:05,122 --> 00:39:07,607
I just want to repay Captain Krit.

463
00:39:09,309 --> 00:39:10,934
Hmm, okay.

464
00:39:15,502 --> 00:39:16,420
Alright.

465
00:39:40,621 --> 00:39:41,691
Hello.

466
00:39:41,691 --> 00:39:43,087
- Hello.
- Hello.

467
00:39:43,144 --> 00:39:45,973
Could I trouble you to give
these snacks to Captain Krit?

468
00:39:45,973 --> 00:39:48,362
- Sure.
- And also,

469
00:39:48,439 --> 00:39:52,511
- could you please change the flowers?
- Sure.

470
00:39:54,920 --> 00:39:55,990
Excuse me.

471
00:39:56,334 --> 00:39:58,858
May I have your name?

472
00:39:58,858 --> 00:40:01,285
- Oh, my name is Som.
- Oh.

473
00:40:01,534 --> 00:40:04,650
May I call you Som?

474
00:40:04,650 --> 00:40:06,389
- Oh, sure.
- Okay.

475
00:40:06,389 --> 00:40:09,926
- Next time I'll bring snacks for you.
- Okay.

476
00:40:10,461 --> 00:40:12,373
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

477
00:41:00,545 --> 00:41:01,692
Hello, Som.

478
00:41:01,941 --> 00:41:03,967
- Hello, Wayu.
- Hello.

479
00:41:03,967 --> 00:41:07,274
I brought salad rolls
and some fruit today.

480
00:41:07,274 --> 00:41:09,587
Please share them around.

481
00:41:09,587 --> 00:41:11,460
- Thank you so much.
- You're welcome.

482
00:41:12,435 --> 00:41:15,819
- And the flowers.
- I'll do it just like before.

483
00:41:15,819 --> 00:41:17,100
Alright.

484
00:41:17,692 --> 00:41:18,438
- Just a sec.
- Okay.

485
00:41:18,438 --> 00:41:19,566
Let me take a picture.

486
00:41:26,199 --> 00:41:28,588
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

487
00:41:28,608 --> 00:41:30,749
- Hello.
- Hmm.

488
00:41:40,517 --> 00:41:42,409
- Hello.
- Hello.

489
00:41:53,630 --> 00:41:55,733
- Excuse me.
- Thank you.

490
00:42:01,009 --> 00:42:02,978
The wound is no longer infected.

491
00:42:03,189 --> 00:42:05,731
All bodily functions are normal.

492
00:42:06,477 --> 00:42:10,395
But the patient isn't responding
to any stimuli at all.

493
00:42:12,307 --> 00:42:13,989
What does it mean, doctor?

494
00:42:14,696 --> 00:42:17,430
The surgery went well, didn't it?

495
00:42:17,698 --> 00:42:19,495
So why is it like this now?

496
00:42:20,202 --> 00:42:22,362
Even though the surgery went well,

497
00:42:23,452 --> 00:42:26,147
it also depends on the patient,

498
00:42:26,223 --> 00:42:29,339
on whether they're
strong enough to recover.

499
00:42:29,932 --> 00:42:31,863
I'd like the family to discuss things

500
00:42:31,863 --> 00:42:35,514
in case the worst happens.

501
00:42:39,700 --> 00:42:41,230
Oh, darling.

502
00:42:41,230 --> 00:42:43,848
Ma'am, please sit down first.

503
00:42:44,556 --> 00:42:47,347
- Sit down.
- Please, just sit down first.

504
00:42:48,283 --> 00:42:50,310
Easy now.

505
00:42:50,539 --> 00:42:53,062
Take deep, slow breaths.

506
00:42:57,440 --> 00:43:00,231
Slow, deep breaths.

507
00:43:07,113 --> 00:43:09,101
Som, I'll go check that room for you.

508
00:43:09,177 --> 00:43:10,936
- Please take care of it for me.
- Sure.

509
00:43:14,205 --> 00:43:15,925
- Oh, Som.
- Hey, Wayu.

510
00:43:16,346 --> 00:43:17,703
How's Captain doing?

511
00:43:17,990 --> 00:43:21,125
Well, he isn't doing very well.

512
00:43:21,507 --> 00:43:24,107
The doctor called the family
to prepare them for the worst.

513
00:43:24,413 --> 00:43:26,649
When Captain's mom heard, she fainted.

514
00:43:26,649 --> 00:43:29,842
She's being treated in a room nearby.
She was really shocked.

515
00:43:35,997 --> 00:43:40,011
Then I'll leave these flowers
for Captain's mother, too.

516
00:43:40,681 --> 00:43:43,223
And here's some fruit,
please help yourselves.

517
00:43:44,714 --> 00:43:45,727
Yes.

518
00:44:34,856 --> 00:44:38,010
Oh, you're awake. How are you feeling?

519
00:44:39,883 --> 00:44:41,642
I feel a bit dizzy.

520
00:44:45,197 --> 00:44:48,065
Who brought these flowers?

521
00:44:48,524 --> 00:44:52,003
Oh, the victim in Captain Krit's case.

522
00:44:52,270 --> 00:44:54,583
He brings flowers
for Captain Krit every day.

523
00:44:54,583 --> 00:44:58,521
When he learned you were sick,
he brought some for you too, Ms. Pimjit.

524
00:45:32,720 --> 00:45:33,618
Yes, Rose.

525
00:45:34,861 --> 00:45:36,677
Krit's condition
has worsened again, Wayu.

526
00:45:40,978 --> 00:45:42,718
Wayu, can you hear me?

527
00:45:44,075 --> 00:45:45,279
I'll head over right away.

528
00:45:55,850 --> 00:45:59,311
I want Norepinephrine,
4 to 250, IV, rate 5.

529
00:45:59,311 --> 00:46:00,304
Yes, doctor.

530
00:46:03,153 --> 00:46:04,395
What's happening?

531
00:46:04,395 --> 00:46:06,995
Oh, the patient is having
a sudden drop in blood pressure.

532
00:46:06,995 --> 00:46:09,824
The doctor will give medication to raise
the blood pressure. Excuse me.

533
00:46:09,824 --> 00:46:11,907
- Okay.
- Darling.

534
00:46:17,452 --> 00:46:19,210
- No. You can't come in yet.
- What's going on?

535
00:46:19,210 --> 00:46:20,892
No, you still can't come in.

536
00:46:20,892 --> 00:46:21,963
- Hey.
- Huh?

537
00:46:23,626 --> 00:46:24,658
What's happening?

538
00:46:25,671 --> 00:46:27,182
Krit's blood pressure dropped suddenly.

539
00:46:27,660 --> 00:46:30,298
- The doctor is helping him.
- Excuse me.

540
00:46:32,630 --> 00:46:34,102
Doctor, the medication is here.

541
00:46:35,210 --> 00:46:35,975
Krit.

542
00:46:37,294 --> 00:46:39,110
I'm safe now. You have to be safe too.

543
00:46:51,077 --> 00:46:52,377
It's all set, doctor.

544
00:46:52,434 --> 00:46:54,823
- Please keep an eye on him for me.
- Of course.

545
00:47:01,189 --> 00:47:02,221
Sorry.

546
00:47:20,745 --> 00:47:24,281
Hey, what are you staring at?
Get him out of here.

547
00:47:25,046 --> 00:47:27,359
No, don't. Let him stay.

548
00:47:29,309 --> 00:47:31,373
Please let him stay with Krit.

549
00:47:31,469 --> 00:47:33,878
I'm begging you, please.

550
00:47:45,156 --> 00:47:45,921
Krit.

551
00:47:48,406 --> 00:47:50,260
You've always wanted
to see me, haven't you?

552
00:47:52,783 --> 00:47:54,217
Well, here I am now.

553
00:47:56,586 --> 00:47:58,433
You don't have to secretly
look for me anymore.

554
00:48:01,634 --> 00:48:04,941
Please wake up and talk to me first.
You haven't even apologized to me yet.

555
00:48:06,968 --> 00:48:09,204
I've only ever heard
about you from others.

556
00:48:11,957 --> 00:48:14,041
You have to wake up
and tell me yourself.

557
00:48:15,226 --> 00:48:17,577
You can't just die and run away
from me like this, Krit.

558
00:48:18,495 --> 00:48:19,297
Krit.

559
00:48:20,081 --> 00:48:20,865
Krit.

560
00:48:47,302 --> 00:48:48,316
Nonsense.

561
00:48:54,605 --> 00:48:55,905
How could I die?

562
00:48:57,224 --> 00:48:58,007
Krit.

563
00:48:59,021 --> 00:49:01,640
Krit.

564
00:49:03,436 --> 00:49:04,985
Krit.

565
00:49:06,055 --> 00:49:08,082
- Krit.
- Call a nurse, hurry!

566
00:49:08,082 --> 00:49:08,923
Yes.

567
00:49:08,923 --> 00:49:10,127
Krit, are you awake?

568
00:49:10,414 --> 00:49:12,288
Krit.

569
00:49:14,906 --> 00:49:15,690
He's awake.

570
00:49:16,378 --> 00:49:17,735
- Krit.
- Excuse me.

571
00:49:17,735 --> 00:49:19,035
Let me check his blood pressure.

572
00:49:23,948 --> 00:49:27,446
His blood pressure looks good now,
and his pulse is normal.

573
00:49:29,645 --> 00:49:30,696
Darling.

574
00:49:36,431 --> 00:49:39,126
Krit, you're awake?

575
00:49:39,757 --> 00:49:40,522
Krit.

576
00:49:51,112 --> 00:49:54,781
Ginseng chicken soup,
and some steamed pumpkin.

577
00:49:54,781 --> 00:49:57,038
I ordered these specially for today.

578
00:49:57,038 --> 00:50:00,135
They're all soft foods.
You'll be able to eat them.

579
00:50:01,645 --> 00:50:03,174
Really? You call this "soft"?

580
00:50:05,201 --> 00:50:07,361
Yeah, this is soft.

581
00:50:07,858 --> 00:50:09,712
Eat up, dear,
so you'll get your strength back.

582
00:50:10,400 --> 00:50:13,765
Is it too hot? If it is, let Mom
cool it down first.

583
00:50:13,898 --> 00:50:15,714
Here, let me cool it down for you first.

584
00:50:15,714 --> 00:50:16,861
No. It's fine.

585
00:50:16,938 --> 00:50:18,314
- I can eat it.
- Okay.

586
00:50:19,499 --> 00:50:22,176
Ouch, it's okay. I will feed you.

587
00:50:25,368 --> 00:50:28,235
The food here is really good.
Take it slow, dear.

588
00:50:29,516 --> 00:50:31,141
Slowly.

589
00:50:35,136 --> 00:50:37,048
Wait.

590
00:50:39,705 --> 00:50:41,827
Careful, dear. It's hot.

591
00:50:45,574 --> 00:50:48,001
- Oh.
- Wait.

592
00:50:57,636 --> 00:50:58,343
Yeah.

593
00:50:58,458 --> 00:51:00,656
Let me wipe that for you, okay?

594
00:51:05,760 --> 00:51:08,112
Okay, eat up.

595
00:51:08,475 --> 00:51:11,247
- Yeah, eat up.
- Eat up, dear.

596
00:51:11,916 --> 00:51:15,241
Dad, Mom, just act normal.
I'm not used to this.

597
00:51:18,262 --> 00:51:19,314
- Hmph.
- Uh.

598
00:51:19,314 --> 00:51:22,697
This is me being normal, you know.

599
00:51:22,965 --> 00:51:25,890
- Ah, no.
- I'm normal too.

600
00:51:29,464 --> 00:51:32,886
- Come on, just a little more, okay?
- Okay.

601
00:51:36,193 --> 00:51:36,958
Mm.

602
00:51:38,812 --> 00:51:39,730
Is it good, dear?

603
00:51:40,666 --> 00:51:42,081
Okay, let's go.

604
00:51:42,081 --> 00:51:43,801
Let's get you moving today.

605
00:51:43,801 --> 00:51:47,548
Bend your knees.
Lift your hips a bit. Up.

606
00:51:47,548 --> 00:51:50,090
Good. Mm.

607
00:51:50,415 --> 00:51:54,047
Good. Now push your legs out.
Stretch them all the way.

608
00:51:55,061 --> 00:51:58,444
Okay, up again. Do it on your own.

609
00:51:58,444 --> 00:52:00,470
Very good. Ah.

610
00:52:01,445 --> 00:52:04,102
Now push up to standing.
Straighten your knees.

611
00:52:04,600 --> 00:52:07,123
Ah, very good.

612
00:52:08,614 --> 00:52:10,258
- Can you manage?
- Oh.

613
00:52:12,475 --> 00:52:13,718
Okay, it's fine then.

614
00:52:16,528 --> 00:52:18,115
Let's do it one more time.
Can you manage?

615
00:52:18,573 --> 00:52:20,982
Try it. Try again. Come on.

616
00:52:23,639 --> 00:52:25,876
Straighten your knees. Push through.

617
00:52:26,373 --> 00:52:27,826
Very good. Mm.

618
00:52:28,456 --> 00:52:30,884
Mm. Sigh.

619
00:52:32,146 --> 00:52:34,899
Step right, then left.

620
00:52:36,026 --> 00:52:38,320
Step with your right, then your left.

621
00:52:40,652 --> 00:52:43,673
Right foot first, then left.

622
00:52:48,624 --> 00:52:51,052
Step right, then left.

623
00:52:55,448 --> 00:52:58,583
Lean forward, press the cane, and stand.

624
00:53:00,476 --> 00:53:03,515
Very good. Now tuck the cane
under your arm.

625
00:53:04,567 --> 00:53:06,842
Good. Keep stepping like that.

626
00:53:08,237 --> 00:53:09,441
Keep going.

627
00:53:11,104 --> 00:53:12,042
Can you manage?

628
00:53:12,614 --> 00:53:14,162
- I can.
- Okay.

629
00:53:27,296 --> 00:53:31,501
You're so stubborn.
You just won't stay in your room.

630
00:53:31,616 --> 00:53:35,267
So? Do you feel better now
that you're outside?

631
00:53:37,083 --> 00:53:38,402
Yeah, a bit better.

632
00:53:40,773 --> 00:53:43,334
At first, I just felt dizzy
and out of it.

633
00:53:44,022 --> 00:53:45,188
But now I feel way better.

634
00:53:46,813 --> 00:53:49,642
Just a bit more physical therapy left.

635
00:53:50,828 --> 00:53:52,988
Soon I'll be back out catching
bad guys and putting them in jail.

636
00:53:54,918 --> 00:53:56,352
How's your wound?

637
00:53:56,639 --> 00:53:57,633
Does it still hurt?

638
00:53:59,430 --> 00:54:02,125
A little, but way better than before.

639
00:54:04,534 --> 00:54:05,260
Here.

640
00:54:05,623 --> 00:54:09,122
When you were out of it,
Wayu came to see you every day.

641
00:54:12,601 --> 00:54:16,309
He brought flowers
to brighten up the room.

642
00:54:16,978 --> 00:54:19,808
Even with school so busy,
he still brought you flowers every day.

643
00:54:21,012 --> 00:54:23,268
But your fiancée?
I haven't seen her once.

644
00:54:23,276 --> 00:54:26,212
Pretty sure she only sent one melon.

645
00:54:32,730 --> 00:54:36,400
So how come now I'm awake,
Wayu hasn't come to see me?

646
00:54:39,172 --> 00:54:40,950
He comes, and they just send him away.

647
00:54:42,709 --> 00:54:45,251
Your dad's chased him off
more times than I can count.

648
00:54:45,748 --> 00:54:49,438
They even put cops at the door,
but he still kept trying.

649
00:54:49,590 --> 00:54:51,082
He couldn't even get in to see you.

650
00:54:51,082 --> 00:54:54,503
So he left the flowers with the nurses,
asked them to change them for you.

651
00:54:58,040 --> 00:54:59,607
Wayu worries about you so much.

652
00:55:30,002 --> 00:55:33,557
Hey! Take it easy.

653
00:55:34,035 --> 00:55:35,584
What's wrong with you?

654
00:55:36,272 --> 00:55:39,139
Captain's awake.
What are you stressing about now?

655
00:55:42,294 --> 00:55:43,842
I don't know how to act.

656
00:55:45,505 --> 00:55:47,493
I don't know what I'm supposed to do.

657
00:55:49,156 --> 00:55:52,521
What do you even need to do?
Just act normal.

658
00:55:54,566 --> 00:55:55,923
So what am I supposed to do?

659
00:55:56,822 --> 00:56:00,377
We already broke up, and his dad
doesn't even like me.

660
00:56:02,786 --> 00:56:06,342
Back when you were visiting him
in the hospital, sending flowers every day,

661
00:56:06,877 --> 00:56:08,215
darn, you were really
going all out, man.

662
00:56:08,750 --> 00:56:11,656
So now he's awake,
what is wrong with you?

663
00:56:21,978 --> 00:56:23,164
What's wrong with you?

664
00:56:24,693 --> 00:56:27,904
- Anyway, they called me for a client.
- Hey.

665
00:56:29,090 --> 00:56:30,141
What now?

666
00:56:32,798 --> 00:56:34,060
I'm booking you for the whole night.

667
00:56:35,838 --> 00:56:38,208
Hey, what is wrong with you?

668
00:56:38,418 --> 00:56:40,043
How are you going to pay for that?

669
00:56:44,268 --> 00:56:47,021
Foei.

670
00:56:50,653 --> 00:56:53,596
- What?
- Let me just sign first.

671
00:56:53,883 --> 00:56:56,120
Just put it on my tab.
I'll settle it later.

672
00:56:56,273 --> 00:56:58,261
Okay, deal.

673
00:56:58,433 --> 00:57:00,497
Come on.

674
00:57:02,466 --> 00:57:03,881
What is this?

675
00:57:04,665 --> 00:57:06,290
Am I working for free today?

676
00:57:07,341 --> 00:57:08,259
Ah.

677
00:57:09,578 --> 00:57:10,400
Okay.

678
00:57:11,202 --> 00:57:12,808
Since I'm working for free anyway,

679
00:57:13,535 --> 00:57:14,643
I'll entertain you myself.

680
00:57:15,427 --> 00:57:16,517
Come on, bottoms up.

681
00:57:18,562 --> 00:57:19,250
Go.

682
00:57:20,359 --> 00:57:21,677
You're not done yet.

683
00:57:35,614 --> 00:57:38,041
(The First Night We Held Hands,
Season Five)

684
00:57:40,488 --> 00:57:45,841
♪Look how long it took
to first hold hands♪

685
00:57:46,051 --> 00:57:50,868
♪It's a miracle
we even found each other♪

686
00:57:51,136 --> 00:57:57,156
♪Don't let us fall apart over
blind anger and misunderstandings♪

687
00:57:57,156 --> 00:58:02,176
♪Look how hard we fought for this love♪

688
00:58:03,656 --> 00:58:04,632
Krit.

689
00:58:04,919 --> 00:58:08,837
I brought your favorite fruit.
I'll peel it for you.

690
00:58:18,300 --> 00:58:20,135
- Mom.
- Hm?

691
00:58:21,664 --> 00:58:23,232
I want to get out of here.

692
00:58:23,671 --> 00:58:26,998
Mm. I know you're bored.

693
00:58:27,246 --> 00:58:29,942
This evening I'll take you out
for a walk in the garden.

694
00:58:35,523 --> 00:58:36,690
It's not that.

695
00:58:38,142 --> 00:58:39,155
Well...

696
00:58:42,348 --> 00:58:43,973
I want to leave the hospital.

697
00:58:47,815 --> 00:58:48,637
Krit.

698
00:58:49,306 --> 00:58:51,275
You only woke up a few days ago.

699
00:58:52,384 --> 00:58:54,506
Wait until you're a bit stronger.

700
00:58:57,622 --> 00:58:58,329
Mom.

701
00:58:59,399 --> 00:59:01,120
I feel a lot better now.

702
00:59:02,286 --> 00:59:05,306
And all my test results came back fine.

703
00:59:05,765 --> 00:59:09,053
I do physical therapy every day,
and I can walk much better now.

704
00:59:13,660 --> 00:59:15,591
- Here.
- Krit.

705
00:59:17,101 --> 00:59:19,662
Don't do this. You're scaring me.

706
00:59:21,766 --> 00:59:23,869
I can walk just fine now, Mom.

707
00:59:25,359 --> 00:59:26,449
Let me go out, please.

708
00:59:27,978 --> 00:59:31,553
I promise. I'll take
good care of myself.

709
00:59:39,849 --> 00:59:40,996
What should we eat, then?

710
00:59:41,034 --> 00:59:42,736
How about fried garlic pork
with a fried egg?

711
00:59:42,736 --> 00:59:44,552
Oh, that again?

712
00:59:44,552 --> 00:59:45,928
- You eat that every day.
- Come on.

713
00:59:46,310 --> 00:59:49,120
- I just like it.
- I'm sick of it.

714
00:59:49,694 --> 00:59:51,433
- Huh?
- What do you want to eat today?

715
00:59:51,969 --> 00:59:54,033
Maybe noodles. Noodles sound better.

716
00:59:54,033 --> 00:59:57,111
- Ugh, it's always this menu.
- Wayu.

717
01:00:05,273 --> 01:00:07,147
- See you, Wayu.
- See you.

718
01:00:12,652 --> 01:00:13,551
Krit.

719
01:00:19,247 --> 01:00:20,184
Wayu.

720
01:00:21,407 --> 01:00:22,440
I'm sorry.

721
01:00:27,238 --> 01:00:29,360
For not telling you the truth back then.

722
01:00:31,405 --> 01:00:32,934
But back then, I really meant it.

723
01:00:33,432 --> 01:00:35,592
I wanted you to find someone better.

724
01:00:37,446 --> 01:00:38,899
But now I know.

725
01:00:40,409 --> 01:00:42,148
That my life means nothing

726
01:00:42,703 --> 01:00:44,481
without you by my side, Wayu.

727
01:00:50,215 --> 01:00:51,898
I don't know if it's too late.

728
01:00:53,924 --> 01:00:55,606
But can you give me one more chance?

729
01:01:06,560 --> 01:01:08,280
What chance are you asking for now?

730
01:01:52,075 --> 01:01:53,012
(Kritsadawut Siriwatmontri
Nov 9, 19/Blood/Code 20839001)

731
01:02:00,429 --> 01:02:01,385
Well...

732
01:02:02,570 --> 01:02:04,156
I love you so much.

733
01:02:06,871 --> 01:02:09,337
But I don't want us to go back
to where we were.

734
01:02:11,211 --> 01:02:13,160
And if one day we break up again,

735
01:02:14,383 --> 01:02:16,372
I'll hurt even more than before.

736
01:02:19,430 --> 01:02:20,558
We're not breaking up again.

737
01:02:21,858 --> 01:02:23,349
I won't break up with you again, Wayu.

738
01:02:35,927 --> 01:02:37,992
Well, I just need a little time.

739
01:02:50,226 --> 01:02:51,393
That's fine.

740
01:03:05,098 --> 01:03:09,248
♪Please, I never wanted to leave you♪

741
01:03:09,248 --> 01:03:12,209
♪And I never wanted to be this far away♪

742
01:03:12,209 --> 01:03:14,304
♪But I accidentally did something♪

743
01:03:15,712 --> 01:03:18,112
(Directed by Banchorn Vorasataree)

744
01:03:19,895 --> 01:03:24,192
♪I just realized that without you♪

745
01:03:24,192 --> 01:03:27,713
♪How much it hurts♪

746
01:03:27,713 --> 01:03:31,872
♪Please, I never wanted to leave you♪

747
01:03:31,872 --> 01:03:34,728
♪As you were♪

748
01:03:34,728 --> 01:03:37,472
♪I won't♪

749
01:03:37,472 --> 01:03:42,489
♪Start the fights like I used to♪

750
01:03:42,489 --> 01:03:48,053
♪Please don't get tired of me just yet♪

751
01:03:48,053 --> 01:03:54,054
♪Come back and let's be us again♪

752
01:03:55,890 --> 01:03:59,598
♪Looking back on our story♪

753
01:04:10,074 --> 01:04:16,076
♪Only when apart did I know♪

754
01:04:16,401 --> 01:04:19,264
♪How deeply we're bound♪

755
01:04:19,264 --> 01:04:23,933
♪My heart's this broken♪

756
01:04:24,220 --> 01:04:26,976
♪I hate that♪

757
01:04:26,976 --> 01:04:32,993
♪No familiar face is left♪

758
01:04:32,993 --> 01:04:39,054
♪When we're far apart♪

759
01:04:39,054 --> 01:04:43,986
♪I finally reflect♪

760
01:04:43,986 --> 01:04:46,720
♪That it was me♪

761
01:04:46,720 --> 01:04:51,616
♪Who chose the wrong path♪

762
01:04:51,616 --> 01:04:57,597
♪One that breaks my own heart♪

763
01:04:57,711 --> 01:05:01,668
♪Honestly, I never wanted to leave you♪

764
01:05:01,668 --> 01:05:04,479
♪I never wanted to be this far away♪

765
01:05:04,479 --> 01:05:06,816
♪But I accidentally did something♪

766
01:05:06,816 --> 01:05:11,968
♪Said things in spite, so wrong♪

767
01:05:11,968 --> 01:05:14,879
♪Shedding tears♪

768
01:05:14,879 --> 01:05:19,867
♪Over the words of my own♪

769
01:05:20,287 --> 01:05:24,263
♪Actually, I want you back♪

770
01:05:24,263 --> 01:05:27,035
♪As you were♪

771
01:05:27,035 --> 01:05:34,413
♪Even though
I always started the fights♪

772
01:05:34,682 --> 01:05:40,435
♪Please don't get tired of me just yet♪

773
01:05:40,435 --> 01:05:46,495
♪Why are you gone so much longer now?♪

774
01:06:07,905 --> 01:06:12,245
♪Please, I never wanted to leave you♪

775
01:06:12,245 --> 01:06:15,399
♪And I never wanted to be this far away♪

776
01:06:15,399 --> 01:06:17,152
♪But I accidentally did something♪

777
01:06:17,152 --> 01:06:22,720
♪I was wrong, crying as I apologize♪

778
01:06:22,720 --> 01:06:27,251
♪I just realized that without you♪

779
01:06:27,251 --> 01:06:30,902
♪How much it hurts♪

780
01:06:30,902 --> 01:06:34,764
♪Please, I never wanted to leave you♪

781
01:06:34,764 --> 01:06:37,574
♪As you were♪

782
01:06:37,574 --> 01:06:40,288
♪I won't♪

783
01:06:40,288 --> 01:06:44,895
♪Start the fights like I used to♪

784
01:06:44,933 --> 01:06:50,917
